#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:1
msgid "Numark N4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:4
msgid ""
"The Numark N4 is a 4-deck DJ controller with seamless integration of "
"external devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:6
msgid "[Manufacturer’s product page](http://www.numark.com/product/n4)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:7
msgid "[Wiki page](https://github.com/mixxxdj/mixxx/wiki/Numark-N4)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:11
msgid "Mapping Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:14
#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:21
msgid "Numark N4 (schematic view)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:23
msgid ""
"This mapping has some unusual features like per Deck shift buttons and "
"multiple pages of hotcues. An annotated, ready-to-print overlay of this "
"mapping can be downloaded for {download}`DIN "
"A3<../../_static/controllers/numark_n4_overlay_a3.pdf>` and {download}`DIN "
"A4<../../_static/controllers/numark_n4_overlay_a4.pdf>` printers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:27
msgid "Definable Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:30
msgid ""
"Some settings in the script can be changed by editing them at the top of the"
" script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:32
msgid ""
"**searchAmplification** Defines the speedup-factor used when using the "
"searchbutton and scrolling.<br> *type:* number<br> *range:* ]0;+∞["
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:36
msgid ""
"**warnAfterTime** Time in seconds before the end of the track in which the "
"controller should warn you.<br> *type:* number<br> *range:* [0;+∞]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:40
msgid ""
"**blinkInterval** Timeinterval for the triangular Leds in ms<br> *type:* "
"number<br> *range:* [20;+∞["
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:44
msgid ""
"**encoderResolution** Percent how much the value changes with each encoder "
"tick<br> *type:* number<br> *range:* ]0;1]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:48
msgid ""
"**resetHotCuePageOnTrackLoad** The Hotcuepage should be reset to 1 when a "
"new Track is loaded into the Deck<br> *type:* boolean<br> *range:* true or "
"false"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:52
msgid ""
"**cueReverseRoll** If [SHIFT]+[CUE] should trigger a reverse_roll<br> "
"*type:* boolean<br> *range:* true or false"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:56
msgid ""
"**rateRanges** An array of rateRanges in percent<br> *type:* array<br> "
"*range:* ]0;3]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:60
msgid "Deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:63
msgid ""
"The Deck consists of the jogwheel, play, cue, the topContainer (which hold "
"the eight square buttons and the four encoders), pitchslider, pitchrange, "
"search, keylock, tap, sync and pitchbend ±."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:66
msgid "Special Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:69
msgid ""
"The mapping features some peculiar features which might not be discoverable "
"by standard trial-and-error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:71
msgid "Shift"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:74
msgid ""
"A shift button is bound to its Deck, which means that you can’t use the "
"shift button of Deck1 to access a shifted function on any of the other three"
" Decks. Moreover the shiftbuttons can also work as toggle switches instead "
"of pushbuttons (enabled via components.js Button.type.powerWindow). This "
"means that if the shiftbutton is pressed for a longer period than 275ms it "
"will bounce back to its original state (like a regular shift-/pushbutton). "
"If the Button was pressed for a shorter period than 275ms, the button will "
"remain in that state until it is pressed again (like a toggling button)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:78
#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:155
msgid "Hotcues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:81
msgid ""
"The four lower buttons of the topContainer are hotcues. They can be changed "
"by using the corresponding Encoder [HOTCUE PAGE]. The current assignment "
"will then be shown for one second in the upper row. Currently up to 4 Pages "
"are supported (with 4 hotcues each)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:84
msgid "Controls"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:87
msgid ""
"Most of these controls behave as expected but they are listed in detail for "
"the sake of completeness anyways."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:89
msgid "Play"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:92
msgid "Default: Starts regular Play.<br> Shifted: Plays Track in reverse."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:95
msgid "Cue"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:98
msgid ""
"Default: Standard Cue.<br> Shifted: reverse roll if shift is enabled (plays "
"in reverse end enables slip) otherwise standard cue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:101
msgid "Pitchbend ±"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:104
msgid ""
"Default: Change rate temporarily.<br> Shifted: Change rate temporarily "
"small."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:107
msgid "Sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:110
msgid ""
"Default: Momentary BPM Sync<br> \\* Short Press: Momentary BPM & Phase Sync"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:113
msgid "Long Press: Toggle Sync Lock"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:115
msgid "Shifted: Toggles magnet (quantize)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:117
msgid "Tap"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:120
msgid ""
"Default: Tap the desired BPM of the Channel<br> Shifted: ^^<br> Note: This "
"functionality is broken until "
"[#1811](https://github.com/mixxxdj/mixxx/pull/1811) gets merged"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:124
msgid "Search/Scratch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:127
msgid ""
"Default: Enable Scratching (otherwise it just works just like moving the Jog"
" without the platter)<br> Shifted: Speeds up platter movement for searching "
"within the track"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:130
msgid "Keylock"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:133
msgid "Default: Toggles track keylock<br> Shifted: Syncs Key"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:136
msgid "Pitch Range"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:139
msgid "Default: Cycles Through pitchranges<br> Shifted: ^^"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:142
msgid "Pitch/Bpm slider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:145
msgid ""
"Default: Normal Pitchslider (Down plays faster; can be changed in the global"
" mixxx preferences)<br> Shifted: ^^"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:148
msgid "TopContainer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:151
msgid ""
"The TopContainer holds four assignable Hotcue buttons, four loop buttons, "
"which can enable FX via Shift, and four Encoderknobs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:158
msgid ""
"Default: set/active Hotcue_X<br> Shift: clear Hotcue_X<br> *visit*\\ "
"[#special_features](#special_features)\\ *for more info on how these work*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:162
msgid "Loop In"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:165
msgid ""
"Default: Presses the Loop In button like in the UI<br> Shifted: Toggles "
"EffectRack1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:168
msgid "Loop Out"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:171
msgid ""
"Default: Presses the Loop Out button like in the UI<br> Shifted: Toggles "
"EffectRack2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:174
msgid "Loop Here"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:177
msgid ""
"Default: Creates a loop at the current position of current Loop Size.<br> "
"Shifted: Toggles Slip"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:180
msgid "Reloop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:183
msgid ""
"Default: De-/Re-activates the last loop<br> Shifted: Jumps to start of last "
"loop and stops playback there"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:186
msgid "FX1 Knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:189
msgid ""
"Default: Controls the Super Knob on EffectRack1.<br> Shifted: Controls the "
"Mix Knob on EffectRack1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:192
msgid "FX2 Knob"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:195
msgid ""
"Default: Controls the Super Knob on EffectRack2.<br> Shifted: Controls the "
"Mix Knob on EffectRack2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:198
msgid "Hotcue Page"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:201
msgid ""
"Default: visit [#special_features](#special_features) for more info on what "
"this encoder does<br> Shifted: Double/Halve current Loop Size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:204
msgid "Beat Jump"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:207
msgid ""
"Default: Jump in the direction turned<br> Shifted: Double/Halve current Beat"
" Jump Size"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:210
msgid "Mixer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:213
msgid ""
"The Mixer features four channels with identical functionality and controls "
"for the library and other miscellaneous features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:215
msgid "Channel"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:218
msgid ""
"A channel consists of a volume fader, a gain knob, knobs for low,mid,high EQ"
" a Loadbutton and a pflButton. These are internally still part of the Deck "
"which is why the shiftbutton of Deck 1 won’t work with the Loadbutton or "
"gainknob of Deck2/3/4."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:221
msgid "Volume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:224
msgid "Default: Channel Volume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:228
msgid "CUE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:231
msgid ""
"Default: Channel Pre-Fader-Listening<br> *these work as usual on the N4: "
"Clicking another one deselect all other.   Press multiple at the same Time "
"to PFL multiple Channels*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:235
msgid "BASS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:238
msgid "Default: EQ Low"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:240
msgid "MID"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:243
msgid "Default: EQ Mid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:245
msgid "TREBLE"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:248
msgid "Default: EQ High"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:250
msgid "GAIN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:253
msgid "Default: Gain<br> Shifted: QuickEffect1 (Usually Filter)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:256
msgid "LOAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:259
msgid "Default: Load Track into Deck<br> Shifted: Eject Track from Deck"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:262
msgid "Library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:265
msgid ""
"The Library is managed via the Library Encoder. **Any** shiftbutton can be "
"used to access shift functionanly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:267
msgid "Turn"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:270
msgid ""
"Default: Move Library Cursor Vertically<br> Shifted: Move Focus between "
"panes<br> *sometimes the focus is stuck somewhere (eg when using the "
"searchbox) and is only recoverable with user intervention via a pointing "
"device.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:274
msgid ""
"**Button** Default: Open/Close Folder / Load Item into first available Deck "
"(Context-dependent)<br> Shift: Maximize Library<br>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:276
msgid "Miscellaneous"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:279
msgid "Crossfader"
msgstr "Crossfader"

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:281
msgid ""
"The Crossfader and its assignment buttons are integrated seamlessly with "
"Mixxx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:283
msgid "Line/PC Input Source"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:286
msgid ""
"Function as expected: Mutes the corresponding Deck in Mixxx if set to Line."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:288
msgid "Crossfader Contour"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:290
msgid ""
"Normal: Uses the crossfader parameters that were present when the mapping "
"was loaded Scratch: Uses Scratch typical parameters for hard cuts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:292
msgid "Cue-Master Mix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:294
msgid ""
"Doesn’t manipulate the mixxx controls. Make sure the head gain is not zero "
"and the mix is set to 100% PFL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:296
msgid "Cue Volume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:298
msgid "Make sure its high enough within mixxx"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:300
msgid "Booth/Gain Volume"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_n4.md:302
msgid "Behaves as expected (but doesn’t manipulate any mixxx controls)."
msgstr ""
